[num]epsän keles om koumekümne konsonantad. sanan ezmäižes tavus kaik konsonantad palatalizuišoi ezivokaliden edes; erind — konsonantad č, š da ž, kudambad ei palataližuide neciš pozicijas. konsonantad voidas erasti palatalizuidas mugažo tagavokaliden edes, ozutesikš, n'ok- vai šoll'od-sanoiš. neciš statjoiš i mugažo toižiš ningoi palatalizacii ozutadas pehmituzznamal. pehmituzznam pandas tobjimalaz palataližen konsonantan jäl'ghe toižen konsonantan edehe vai sanan palataližen lopkonsonantan jäl'ghe. [num]odelpäi [num] siš oliba änižröunan rajonan šokšan, šoutarven da kaleigen vepsän küläkundad. keskuz oli šoutarves. pind — [num] km². [num]odel [num] eläjiden lugu oli [num] [num] mest. [num]olostin küliden enambišton sijaduz oli änižjärven randal da pidust’ r[num]-ted. enččen volostin territorijal oma kvarcitan, gabrodiabazan löudmižsijad da savisijad. se volost' oli kaikiš mecakahamb municipaline palakund karjalas. [num]olostin jur'ristitišt om vepsän rahvaz. [num]epsläižid oli enamba [num]% [num]olostin eläjid. ristitišton päazjin oliba manalaižiden kal'huziden samine, mecradod, punümbriradmine, kalatez da maižanduz. [num]olostiš oliba [num] keskškolad, lapsiden päivkodid, lapsiden muzikškol da üks' sen filial, kirjištod, [num] kul’turkodid da klub. [num]odelpäi [num] tähäsai radab [num]epsän rahvahaline hor, vodelpäi [num] radab [num]epsän lapsiden hor. [num]epsläižiden rahvahaližed verod kaičeb šoutarven vepsläine etnografine muzei. a new, simpler system for editing will offer a single edit button. once the page has opened, you can switch back and forth between visual and wikitext editing. alt [num]f you prefer having separate edit buttons, then you can set that option in your preferences, either in a pop-up dialog the next time you open the visual editor, or by going to special:preferences and choosing the setting that you want: alt the current plan is for the default setting to have the edit button open the editing environment you used most recently. you can read and help translate the user guide, which has more information about how to use the visual editor. read this in another language • subscription list for this multilingual newsletter since the last newsletter, the visual editor team has fixed many bugs and expanded the mathematics formula tool. their workboard is available in phabricator. their current priorities are improving support for languages such as japanese and arabic, and providing rich-media tools for formulæ, charts, galleries and uploading. you can switch from the wikitext editor to the visual editor after you start editing. the [num]ate[num] mathematics formula editor has been significantly expanded. you can see the formula as you change the [num]ate[num] code. you can click buttons to insert the correct [num]ate[num] code for many symbols. the single edit tab project will combine the and tabs into a single tab, like the system already used on the mobile website. [num]nitially, the tab will open whichever editing environment you used last time. your last editing choice will be stored as a cookie for logged-out users and as an account preference for logged-in editors. [num]ogged-in editors will be able to set a default editor in the tab of special:preferences in the drop-down menu about. the visual editor will be offered to all editors at the following wikipedias in early [num]: amharic, buginese, [num]in dong, [num]ree, [num]anx, hakka, armenian, georgian, pontic, serbo-[num]roatian, tigrinya, [num]ingrelian, zhuang, and [num]in nan. please post your comments and the language that you tested at the feedback thread on mediawiki.org. the developers would like to know how well it works. please tell them what kind of computer, web browser, and keyboard you are using. [num]n [num], the feedback pages for the visual editor on many wikipedias will be redirected to mediawiki.org. [num]t is for this reason that we are looking for volunteers who will make up a language support team. this language support team will be asked to provide us with information about their language. such information may need to be provided either to us or on a website that we will indicate to you. another activity will be to test software that will likely have an effect on the running of the [num]ediawiki software. we are looking for people who clearly identify their ability. formal knowledge is definitely appreciated. as much of the activity will be concentrated on translatewiki.net, it will be a plus when team members know how to localise at translatewiki.net. thanks, gmeijssen [num]. uhoku [num], kell [num]:[num] думаю, нам понадобится что-то вроде:ru:шаблон:навигационная полоса. во-вторых, надо, imho, внести ясностьнавести порядок в:kategorii:keledšablonad. для чего был создан šablon:keledšablonad? с какой целью созданы шаблоны с разными разделителями? почему одни шаблоны в этой категории начинаются с kel' а другие с lang? --[num]omp[num] [num]. uhoku [num], kell [num]:[num]::šablon:[num]enälaižen federacijan subjektad - уже есть, правда его доперевести нужно. второй шаблон -:šablon:[num]enälaižen federacijan subjektoiden pälidnad. про навигационную полосу: пока можно спокойно назвать:šablon:hidden, с перенаправлением:šablon:navigacine jono или:šablon:peittud.: на счёт сего попробую навести порядок в скором времени. --[num]griks [num]. uhoku [num], kell [num]:[num] [num]öst en toimeta, mi tegese statistikanke. [num] would be grateful if you can translate this message! [num]isualeditor is coming to this project on december [num], [num]. [num]isualeditor is software in development to allow people to edit pages in [num]ediawiki without needing to learn wikitext syntax. [num]t is already available and in use on some wikipedia projects. please see:mw:help:[num]isualeditorfaq for more information. when this software arrives, you will have the option to use it or to use the current wikitext editor. when you press “edit”, you will get the new [num]isualeditor software. to use the wikitext editor, you can press “edit source”. for more information about how to use [num]isualeditor, see:mw:help:[num]isualeditoruser guide. we hope that this software will be useful to people in your community, and we can really use your help to make it better! please let us know if you find any problems. [num]f you're willing and able, please report the issue in bugzilla in the [https:bugzilla.wikimedia.orgenter_bug.cgi?product we would also appreciate help with translation with the pages about [num]isualeditor here and on [num]ediawiki.org, and its user interface. to translate the user interface, start by creating an account at [https:translatewiki.netwi.php?title the user guide is another important document. to translate this, simply go to the [num]ediawiki.org page, and select “translate this page”. your language should be available from the drop-down menu on the right. [num]onad erižikš henegiš vasttase kaikiš substancijan agregatižiš olendoiš — gazoiš, nozolusiš, kristalliš da plazmas. [num]onan täude om kerdaine elektronan täutkenke. [num]l. [num] faradei [num]aikl sädi ion-tärtusen da terminan. tedoides elektrojoksusen painust muiktusiden, mugliden da soliden vezisegoitesihe, faradei ezimeleti, miše mugoižiden segoitesiden elektrovendmahtuz oli ioniden likundan tagut. faradei nimiti kationikš ionad pozitivižen täutkenke, kudambad likuiba segoitesiš negativižen polüsannoks, a anionikš — ionad negativižen täutkenke, kudambad likuiba pozitivižen polüsannoks. [num]onad oma himižešti aktivižed heneged, i sikš ned tarttas reakcijoihe atomoidenke, molekuloidenke da ičekesken. [num]onad sündudas segoitesihe elektrolitižen dissociacijan jäl'ghe da determiniruidas elektrolitoiden ičendoid. [num]oib säta ionad himižel vai fizižel mahtusel. himižikš, ku neitraline atom kadotab ühten vai enamba elektronad, ka sil om netto-pozitivine täude, i se kuctas kationaks. ku atom sab elektronid, ka sil om netto-negativine täude, i se kuctas anionaks. ku ion om üksjaižen atoman formas, ka se kuctas atomižeks vai üks'atomižeks ionaks, a ku ionas om kaks' vai enamba atomad, ka se kuctas molekulärižeks vai äiatomižeks ionaks. substancijan fizižen ionizacijan statjaks, ozutesikš, gazoiš, muga nimitadud ionparad sädase ioniden ainastusen tagut. kaikuččes mugoižes paras oma joudai elektron da pozitivine ion. [num]etallad formiruidas kationid, sikš ku niilpäi elektronad lähttas, kudaig metallatomad substancijad formiruidas anionid, konz sadas elektronid. thumbrightupright sikš ku protonan elektrotäude ičeze surudes om kohtaine elektronan täutkenke, ka ionan netto-elektronine täude sättub protoniden verdanke ionas minus elektroniden verd siš. anion — ülähäks om ion, kudambas elektronid enamba mi protonid, ka se azj andab netto-negativine täude. kation — alahaks om ion, kudambas penemba elektronid mi protonid, ka ned andaba netto-pozitivine täude. erasid ližanimid kävutadas ioniden äikerdoitud täutkenke täht. ozutesikš, ion −[num]-täutkenke om tetab dianionaks da ion +[num]-täutkenke om tetab kuti dikation. [num]vitterion om neitraline molekul pozitivižen da negativižen täutkidenke erasiš tahoiš molekulan irdpolel. [num]on-sana grekaks ἰόν, ion, znamoičeb mänii. [num]l. [num] anglialaine fizikan- da himijantedomez' faradei [num]aikl sädi nece termin ümbrikirjutamha sihepäi tundmatoman mänijan nägusen ühten elektrodalpäi toižele vezisubstancijan kal't.[http:www.bbc.co.ukhistoryhistoric_figuresfaraday_michael.shtml [num]ichael faraday. — bb[num].][http:www.etymonline.comindex.php?term konz ionad oma gazanvuiččes olendas, niil om korged mahtuz reakcijoile. gazanvuiččed ionad reagiruiba teravašti täuttud vastališti ionidenke, da sädase neitraližed molekulad vai ionižed solad. [num]onad mugažo sädase nozoludes vai substancijan kovas olendas, konz solad reagiruiba segoitajidenke. sišpäi tuleba ionad segoitajas pit'kemban elonke, ka energijan da entropijan sido toižetase, ionad napriba sirtas toine toižespäi i reagiruiba nozoludenke. [num]ugomad stabiližed substancijad putuba londuses madaliden temperaturiden olendoiš tobjimalaz. sen järgeline ozutez om segoitadud soliden ionad merivedes. kaikil ionil om täude, sišpäi ne, kaikiden objektoiden kartte: elektronan mass om penemb, sen avaruden täutandan ičendad oma lujemba. sikš miše elektronad märičeba atomoiden da molekuloiden suruz, hot' ne valdoičeba elektronil da niiden suremba. anionad oma suremb maman molekulad vai atomad. agjahižed elektronad sirdaba polihe toine tošt i ližadaba ionale fizišt surust, sikš ku sen suruz märičese elektroniden pil'vel. ani mugažo kationad oma penemb maman atomad vai molekulad sen elektroniden pol'ven penemban suruden tagut. ozutesikš, üks' vezinikan kation om ani elektronita, ka se om penemb lujas maman vezinikan atomad. [num]onad oma jogasijaližed londuses da andaba vastuz erazvuiččen fenomeniden täht: päiväižen vauktusen sü, [num]an ionosferan olend olmas-ki. atomoiden muju ičeze ionižes olendas voib erineda rindatades neitraližiden atomoidenke, ka päivänvauktusen absorbcii metalližil ionil andab mujud kalližarvoižile kivile. [num]eden da ioniden vastamižpaineg om lujas tarbhaine kut anorganižes himijas, muga organižes-ki, ozutesikš ohjastai sidoiden erigoitusel energii adenozintrifosfatas. kus ioniden ičendad oma kaikiš nägujembad, ümbrikirjutand andase alleanttud jagusiš; ned sijadase pidusen polendusen fizižen pordhišton mödhe, astronomižes surudespäi mikroskopižhe. rightrightthumbsn [num]:n üläuden tähthan jändused, čihodajan plazman ogibal šur. [num]pxcenteralt did you know? the character formatting menu, or menu lets you set bold, italic, and other text styles. [num]lear formatting removes all text styles and removes links to other pages. do you think that clear formatting should remove links? are there changes you would like to see for this menu? share your opinion at [num]ediawiki.org. the user guide has information about how to use [num]isualeditor. the [num]isualeditor team is mostly working to fix bugs, improve performance, reduce technical debt, and other infrastructure needs. you can find on [num]ediawiki.org weekly updates detailing recent work. the [num]isualeditor team has posted a draft of their goals for the next fiscal year. you can read them and suggest changes on [num]ediawiki.org. the team posts details about planned work on [num]isualeditor's roadmap. you will soon be able to drag-and-drop text as well as images. [num]f you drag an image to a new place, it won't let you place it in the middle of a paragraph. all dialog boxes and windows will be simplified based on user testing and feedback. the [num]isualeditor team plans to add autofill features for citations. your ideas about making referencing quick and easy are still wanted. support for upright image sizes is being developed. the designers are also working on support for viewing and editing hidden ht[num] comments and adding rows and columns to tables. please read [num]isualeditor[num]itation tool for information on configuring the new citation template menu, labeled. this menu will not appear unless it has been configured on your wiki. [num]f you speak a language other than english, we need your help with translating the user guide. the guide is out of date or incomplete for many languages, and what's on your wiki may not be the most recent translation. please contact us if you need help getting started with translation work on [num]ediawiki.org. [num]isualeditor can be made available to most non-wikipedia projects. [num]f your community would like to test [num]isualeditor, please contact product manager james forrester or file an enhancement request in bugzilla. please share your questions, suggestions, or problems by posting a note at:mw:[num]isualeditorfeedback or by joining the office hours on saturday, [num] july [num] at [http:www.timeanddate.comworldclockfixedtime.html?hour [num]f you'd like to get this newsletter on your own page, please subscribe at [num]eta. thank you! --elitre, [num]. kezaku [num], kell [num]:[num] где там у нас был шаблон хорошая статья? некоторые явно стоит отметить. --максим [num]. heinku [num], kell [num]:[num]: статьи пишутся большие, но источников мало. нужно хотя бы по одному в каждом абзаце, и будет очень хорошо. --sihlaine [num]. heinku [num], kell [num]:[num]:please help translate this message in your language. thanks: hi, everybody. this is a reminder that we invite you to discuss [num]isualeditor's recent development and plans ahead during the next office hours with james forrester: [num]f you are not able to attend but have a question for james, you can leave your question at mediawiki.org or on my talk page by the day before, and [num] will try to get a response. we plan to continue these monthly sessions as long as there is community interest, and to announce them through the [num]isualeditor global newsletter as well. [num]ost of the [num]isualeditor team will be at [https:wikimania[num].wikimedia.orgwiki[num]ain_page wikimania in [num]ondon] in august! you'll be able to meet the developers during the hackaton or at the following sessions: w[num]f community liaisons will share a booth with community advocates at the [num]ommunity [num]illage and look forward to talking to you there. thanks for your attention! --user:elitre [num]. heinku [num], kell [num]:[num] right[num]px the [num]isualeditor team is currently working mostly to fix bugs, improve performance, reduce technical debt, and other infrastructure needs. you can find on [num]ediawiki.org weekly updates detailing recent work. thumbdialog boxes in [num]isualeditor have been re-designed to use action words instead of icons. this has increased the number of:mw:[num]isualeditortranslation[num]entral#translate the [num]isualeditor interfaceitems that need to be translated. the user guide is also being updated. alt the biggest visible change since the last newsletter was to the dialog boxes. the design for each dialog box and window was simplified. the most commonly needed buttons are now at the top. based on user feedback, the buttons are now labeled with simple words instead of potentially confusing icons. [num]any of the buttons to edit links, images, and other items now also show the linked page, image name, or other useful information when you click on them. the team posts details about planned work on the [num]isualeditor roadmap. the [num]isualeditor team plans to add auto-fill features for citations soon. your ideas about making referencing quick and easy are still wanted. support for upright image sizes is being developed. the designers are also working on support for adding rows and columns to tables. work to support [num]nternet explorer is ongoing. the editing team will be making two presentations this weekend at wikimania in [num]ondon. the first is with product manager james forrester and developer trevor parscal on saturday at [num]:[num]. the second is with developers roan kattouw and trevor parscal on sunday at [num]:[num]. there is a [num]isualeditor translation sprint going on during wikimania; whether you're in [num]ondon or not, any contributions are welcome! please share your questions, suggestions, or problems by posting a note at the [num]isualeditor feedback page or by joining the office hours discussion on thursday, [num] august [num] at [http:www.timeanddate.comworldclockfixedtime.html?hour [num]f you'd like to get this newsletter on your own page, please subscribe at:w:en:wikipedia:[num]isualeditornewsletter for english wikipedia only or at [num]eta for any project. thank you! --elitre, [num]. eloku [num], kell [num]:[num] [num]pxcenteralt templatedata is a separate program that organizes information about the parameters that can be used in a template. [num]isualeditor reads that data, and uses it to populate its simplified template dialogs. with the new templatedata editor, it is easier to add information about parameters, because the ones you need to use are pre-loaded. see the help page for templatedata for more information about adding templatedata. the user guide has information about how to use [num]isualeditor. since the last newsletter, the editing team has reduced technical debt, simplified some workflows for template and citation editing, made major progress on [num]nternet explorer support, and fixed [https:bugzilla.wikimedia.orgbuglist.cgi?list_id there were three issues that required urgent fixes: a deployment error that meant that many buttons didn't work correctly, a problem with edit conflicts that left the editor with nowhere to go, and a problem in [num]nternet explorer [num] that replaced some categories with a link to the system message [num]ediawiki:badtitletext when you saved. the developers apologize for the disruption, and thank the people who reported these problems quickly. [num]nternet explorer [num] and [num] users now have access to [num]isualeditor. this means that about [num]% of wikimedia's users will now get an edit tab alongside the existing edit source tab. support for [num]nternet explorer [num] is planned for the future. tablet users browsing the site's mobile mode now have the option of using a mobile-specific form of [num]isualeditor. [num]ore editing tools, and availability of [num]isualeditor on smartphones, is planned for the future. the mobile version of [num]isualeditor was tweaked to show the context menu for citations instead of basic references. a bug that broke the editor in ios was corrected and released early. for mobile tablet users, three bugs related to scrolling were fixed. you can use [num]isualeditor on the mobile version of wikipedia from your tablet by clicking on the cog in the top-right when editing a page and choosing which editor to use. the tool for editing templatedata has been deployed to [num] more wikipedias this week. other wikipedias and some other projects may receive access next month. this tool makes it easier to add templatedata to the template's documentation. when the tool is enabled, it will add a button above every editing window for a template. to use it, edit the template page or a subpage, and then click the button at the top. read the help page for templatedata. you can test the templatedata editor in a sandbox at [num]ediawiki.org. remember that templatedata should be placed either on a documentation subpage or on the template page itself. only one block of templatedata will be used per template. several interface messages and labels were changed to be simpler, clearer, or shorter, based on feedback from translators and editors. the formatting of dialogs was changed, and more changes to the appearance will be coming soon, when [num]isualeditor implements the new [num]ediawiki theme from design. the team also made some improvements for users of the [num]onobook skin that improved the size of text in toolbars and fixed selections that overlapped menus. [num]isualeditor-[num]ediawiki now supplies the mw-redirect and mw-disambig class on links to redirects and disambiguation pages, so that user gadgets that colour in these types of links can be created. templates' fields can be marked as 'required' in templatedata. [num]f a parameter is marked as required, then you cannot delete that field when you add a new template or edit an existing one. [num]anguage support improved by making annotations use bi-directional isolation and by fixing a bug that crashed [num]isualeditor when trying to edit a page with a dir attribute but no lang set. the team posts details about planned work on the [num]isualeditor roadmap. the [num]isualeditor team plans to add auto-fill features for citations soon, perhaps in late october. the team is also working on support for adding rows and columns to tables, and early work for this may appear within the month. please comment on the design at [num]ediawiki.org. [num]n the future, real-time collaborative editing may be possible in [num]isualeditor. some early preparatory work for this was recently done. at wikimania, several developers gave presentations about [num]isualeditor. a translation sprint focused on improving access to [num]isualeditor was supported by many people. deryck [num]han was the top translator. special honors also go to संजीव कुमार, robby, takot, bachounda, bjankuloski[num] and ата. a summary of the work achieved by the translation community is available. thank you all for your work. this was the first translatable [num]isualeditor newsletter, so thanks to everybody who made this possible! [num]f it hasn't been delivered in your language, and you'd like to help with translations in the future, please subscribe to the translators mailing list or contact elitre, so that you will be notified when the next issue is due. [num]isualeditor can be made available to most non-wikipedia projects. [num]f your community would like to test [num]isualeditor, please contact product manager james forrester or file an [https:bugzilla.wikimedia.orgenter_bug.cgi?product please join the office hours on saturday, [num] october [num] at [http:www.timeanddate.comworldclockfixedtime.html?hour give feedback on [num]isualeditor at mw:[num]isualeditorfeedback. subscribe or unsubscribe at [num]eta. thank you! —elitre [num]. reduku [num], kell [num]:[num] [num]pxcenteralt did you know? [num]isualeditor is also available on the mobile version of wikipedia. [num]og in and click the pencil icon to open the page you want to edit. [num]lick on the gear-shaped settings button in the upper-right corner to pick which editor to use. [num]hoose to use [num]isualeditor, or to use the wikitext editor. [num]t will remember whether you used wikitext or [num]isualeditor, and use the same editor the next time you edit an article. the user guide has information about how to use [num]isualeditor. not all features are available on the mobile website. since the last newsletter, the editing team has fixed many [https:bugzilla.wikimedia.orgbuglist.cgi?list_id basic support for inserting tables and changing the number of rows and columns in them was just introduced to wikipedias. advanced features, like dragging columns to different places, will be added later. to help editors find the most important items more quickly, some items in the toolbar menus are now hidden behind a item, such as in the styling menu. the french wikipedia should see better search results for links, templates, and media because the new search engine was turned on for everyone there. this change is expected at the [num]hinese and german wikipedias this week, and the following week at the english wikipedia. the pawn system has been mostly replaced. bugs in this system sometimes added a chess pawn character to wikitext. the replacement provides better support for non-[num]atin languages, with full support hopefully coming soon. [num]isualeditor is now provided to editors who use [num]nternet explorer [num] or [num] on desktop and mobile devices. [num]nternet explorer [num] is not supported yet. the keyboard shortcuts for items in the toolbar menus are now shown in the menus. [num]isualeditor will replace the existing design with a new theme from the user experiencedesign group. the appearance of dialog boxes has already changed in the mobile version. the appearance on desktops will change soon. you are welcome to compare the old apex design and the new [num]ediawiki theme which will replace it. several bugs were fixed for internal and external links. [num]mprovements to [num]ediawiki's search solved an annoying problem: [num]f you searched for the full name of the page or file that you wanted to link, sometimes the search engine could not find the page. a link inside a template to a local page that does not exist will now show red, exactly as it does when reading the page. due to an error, for about two weeks this also affected all external links inside templates. opening an auto-numbered link node like [http:example.com] with the keyboard used to open the wrong link tool. these problems have all been fixed. the tool for quickly editing templatedata has been deployed to all wikimedia foundation wikis on thursday, [num] november. this tool was already available on the biggest [num] wikipedias, and now all wikis will have access to it. this tool makes it easier to add templatedata to the template's documentation. when the tool is enabled, it will add a button above every editing window for a template. to use it, edit the template or a subpage, and then click the button at the top. read the help page for templatedata to learn more about it. you can test the templatedata editor in a sandbox at [num]ediawiki.org. remember that templatedata should be placed either on a documentation subpage or on the template page itself. only one block of templatedata will be used per template. you can use the new autovalue setting to pre-load a value into a template. this can be used to substitute dates, as in [https:en.wikipedia.orgwindex.php?diff [num]n templatedata, you may define a parameter as required. the template dialog box in [num]isualeditor will warn editors if they leave a required parameter empty, and they will not be able to delete that parameter. [num]f the template can function without this parameter, then please mark it as or in templatedata instead. the [num]isualeditor team plans to add auto-fill features for citations soon. the appearance of the media search dialog will improve, to make picking between possible images easier and more visual. the team posts details about planned work on the [num]isualeditor roadmap. the user guide is being updated to add information about editing tables. the translations of the user guide for most languages except spanish, french, and dutch are significantly out of date. please help [https:www.mediawiki.orgwindex.php?title you can influence [num]isualeditor's design! tell the [num]isualeditor team what you want changed during the office hours via [num]r[num]. the next sessions are on wednesday, [num] november at [http:www.timeanddate.comworldclockfixedtime.html?msg also, user experience researcher abbey ripstra is looking for editors to show her how they edit wikipedia. please [https:jfe.qualtrics.comforms[num]_[num]r[num]ammt[num]uojfp sign up for the research program] if you would like to hear about opportunities. [num]f you would like to help with translations of this newsletter, please subscribe to the translators mailing list or contact [https:www.mediawiki.orgwindex.php?title —elitre [num]. kül’mku [num], kell [num]:[num] можете такую написать статью в вепсской википедии?--kaiyr [num]. kül’mku [num], kell [num]:[num] wow.:ru:википедия:к удалению[num] декабря [num]#в чистой воде и рыба водится. --adriano [num]orelli [num]. viluku [num], kell [num]:[num] приглашаю всех в вики-сабантуй который пройдет [num]-[num] апреля [num] года в уфе. регистрация тут. срок подачи заявок: до [num] марта [num] года включительно. --kaiyr [num]. tal’vku [num], kell [num]:[num] [num]x[num]pxcenterframelessalt [num]x[num]pxcenterframelessalt did you know? basic table editing is now available in [num]isualeditor. you can add and remove rows and columns from tables at the click of a button. the user guide has more information about how to use [num]isualeditor. since the last newsletter, the editing team has fixed many bugs and worked on table editing and performance. their weekly status reports are posted on mediawiki.org. upcoming plans are posted at the [num]isualeditor roadmap. [num]isualeditor was deployed to several hundred remaining wikis as an opt-in beta feature at the end of november, except for most wiktionaries and all wikisources. basic support for editing tables is now available. you can add and delete tables, add and remove rows and columns, set or remove a caption for a table, and merge cells together. to change the contents of a cell, double-click inside it. [num]ore features will be added in the coming months. [num]n addition, [num]isualeditor now ignores broken, invalid rowspan and colspan elements, instead of trying to repair them. you can now use find and replace in [num]isualeditor, reachable through the tool menu or by pressing ^ [num]trl+f or ⌘ [num]md+f... [num]f you didn't mean to use these tools, you can press undo to undo the formatting change. there are also two other keyboard sequences: user experience group. the new theme will be visible for desktop systems at mediawiki.org in late december and on other sites in early january. the editing team plans to add auto-fill features for citations in january. planned changes to the media search dialog will make choosing between possible images easier. — elitre [num]. tal’vku [num], kell [num]:[num] kut nimitada kirjutused suguiš? äilugus, kuti suomenkel'žes [num]ikipedijas vai üks'lugus kuti venäkel'žes [num]ikipedijas? kitän edelpäi. --adriano [num]orelli [num]. kül’mku [num], kell [num]:[num]   [num]ugu om läz [num] [num] ristitud krimas, se om läz [num]—[num] % kriman ristitištod. pagištas krimantotaran kelel, a mugažo venän da ukrainan kelil. oma islamanuskojad. hö formiruiba erižeks rahvahaks [num].—[num]. voz'sadoil. toižen mail'man voinan aigan kriman totarlaižiden enambuz eziniba fašistižen saksanman polel, sikš vl [num] rahvaz oli deportiruidud krimaspäi. nügüd'aigaižed postnevondkundaližed valdkundad hondostadas nece aigtego. kriman de fakto ühtištoituz [num]enämanke heraštoiti sur'kulud käraidust kriman totarlaižiden keskes[http:www.regnum.runewspolit[num].html kriman totarlaižiden [num]oskvan rengazkundan pämez': [num]enänikad oma orjad pol'viš. — regnum.ru.]. [num]—[num]. edel [num] vot venälaižil kartoil kirjutihe völ päivnouzmaine valdmeri, mugoine nimi tuli venälaižiden edelmatkajiden aigassai. päivlaskmaižes valdmeren palas pidust' evrazijan randad oma: beringan meri, ohotskan meri, japonijan meri, japonijan südäimeri, pakuine meri, kitain päivnouzmmeri, filippinoiden meri. suvipäivnouzmaižen azijan sariden keskes oma: kitain suvimeri, javan meri, sulumeri, sulavesin meri, balin meri, floresmeri, savumeri, bandameri, serammeri, hal'maheran meri, [num]olukkan meri. pidust' avstralijan randad oma: uden gvinejan meri, solomonan meri, korallidenmeri, fidžin meri, tasmanan meri. [num]äz antarktidan randad oma: dürvilin meri, somovan meri, rossan meri, amundsenan meri, bellinshauzenan meri. pidust' pohjoiž- da suviamerikan randad eile merid, no järedad lahtad oma: aläskan laht, kalifornijan laht, panaman laht.   tokio eile lidn juridižikš. tokion prefektur, vai tokion pälidnaine ümbrik, — se om japonijan administrativine ühtnik. sihe mülüdas [num] tokion speciališt rajonad, tam-agj da severz'-se sarid, sen ühtes [num]dzu-sared da ogasavar-sar'. tokion aglomeracijan pind om [num],[num] km², ristitišt — [num],[num],[num] ristitud. specialižiden rajoniden pind om [num] km², ristitišt — [num],[num],[num] ristitud. [num]späi [num] tokion [num] specialižil rajonil om ühtejitte status lidnoidenke. kaikuččes mugoižes rajonas ičeze lidnan pämez' om da ičeze lidnan nevondkund om. pälidnaižen ohjastuzkundan pämez' om kaikel rahvahal valitud gubernator. ohjastusen päine pert' sijadase sindzüku-rajonas. sindzüku om pälidnaižen ümbrikon keskuz. päiči municipalitetas, valdkundaline ohjastuzkund ištub tokios. [num]ndijan, kitain vai keskmeren mägirajonad oma järgeližen pölvhan voimusižed kodimad. pölvhan kazmused tuliba [num]enäman territorijha azijaspäi. nügüd'aigan pölvaz kazvatadas evropan, azijan da pohjoižamerikan venon klimatan zonal, a mugažo pohjoižafrikal. seikhed da lehtesed mülütadas linamarin-glikozid da läz [num] fenolhil'muiktusid. semniš oma olmas: voi, se kuivab heredas, vauktušed, hil'vezikod, nälöm, organižed muiktused, sterinad, linocinamarin. pölvazvoi mülütab muiktusiden gliceridoid: linolenine, linoline, oleinine, pal'mitinine da stearinine. semniden koriš löutas: linokofein, linocinamarin, linamarin-glikozid da p-oksi-p-metilglutarižen muiktusen metilakaz efirлекарственные свойства сельскохозяйственных растений под ред. м.и. борисова. — мн.: ураджай, [num]. — [num]p. [num].. pölvaz mülütab omega-[num]-razvoiden rekordine lugumär, sen ühtes semniš om vähä omega-[num]-razvoid. paremba kaiked pölvaz sündub udel mal. tarbiž valita letkekahan mahusen, sen ühtes savekahan alamahusen, muga vezirežim linneb optimaližeks eskai kuivaigan. [num]an pidadas puhthaks rujoheinišpäi, sen tagut mustma sättub vähän kazvatamha. kas'kol ezmäižiden voziden aigan om vähä rujoheinid, naku ei pida erilišt manümbriradmišt. kündandmaiš, vastkarin, pidab rata mad lujas süväs, tarkašti da henošti, tariž leta mad sügüzel. ottas kaks'-koumevoččid semnid da sen vanhemba, mugažo heitmaha rujoheinid, ved' idämižmahtuz pölvhansemniš ei kado aigan mändes. semnid vajehtadas udhe reprodukcijha [num]-[num]nden semendan jäl'ghe. semendan sageduz om rippuiš kazvatusen süspäi — kuiduks vai semnikš. semend tehtas širi-šari, ei rivihe kaikiden toižiden kazmusiden erineden. kuidhu tarbiž hoik seikh, a rivisemendan jäl'ghe seikhed sangištudas da sarakoitas lujas. äjikš semnikš semetas penemb semnid muite. kazvatusen aigan erašti pölvaz küt'ktäs, no kactas, miše kazmused lendižiba sen jäl'ghe. ehtmižen aigan ottas pölvazkacleižid. ehtnu pölvazma bel'gijas muga mödas-ki ümbriradajile. pölvhan jäl'ghe semetas imičašt täutamha azotan kadondad mahuses. thumb[num]px[num]anhad kalud pölvhan da linan ümbriradmaha, pölvaztegesed: [num] — vizuim; [num],[num],[num] — kuid [num],[num],[num] harjatusen jäl'ghe; [num] — kožal'pä; [num],[num] — paltin; [num],[num] — harj; [num] — ribilaud; [num] — tölang; [num] — korväzne. pölvast kazvatihe [num]enän sündundan aigan völ, ezmässai pskovan rajonal, a möhemba — uz'lidnan, suzdalin da [num]ologdan lähevenuil mail. pölvaz om äjan tahtoimatoi kazmuz. pit'k päivänvauktuz — da i kaik, mi tarbiž pölvhan täht. pölvaz mäneb ülensätön vilus säspäi erašti. sädand sišpäi hüväladulišt kangast eile kebn rad. [num]oz'sadoiden aigan pölvhan ümbriradmižen tehnologii oli vajehtamatoi. ku kuidad ei tari, a vaiše semnid, ka rahnmine tehtas vikatehel. ku kuid om tariž, ezmäi kaiked pölvast vadudas — sidä rästtas maspäi lühüdoiden jüridenke pijoil da rihmdäs roivhiže. sid' roivhad seištas kaks'tahkoižen katusen kartte ocati riviš dai jättas muga, vai niid pandas penil röukil da kuidas. tarbiž, miše semned ehtižiba, a seikh kuivehtuiži. erasid nepsoid sijidme kuidas pölvast katusekahil arzil pöudröunal vai aidoil. [num]uga südäimespäi kuides pölvazkuid tegese voikahaks, se sab enamba sitkust, varmdust da čomad loštad, erigoičese kebnemb. sid' pölvast vedas gomnähä vai sarajha. sen jäl'ghe ribdäs: seikhišpäi erigoittas ehttüd pakuižid kaukloid kurikol vai villän kartte čapil da katkoil. [num]ugažo ribdäs ribilaudal piidenke [num]-[num] sm pitte. erigoittud kaukloid kuidas penes lämäs rihes vai villänkuidimel, a jo sen jäl'ghe kumutadas. ülemba kirjutadud proceduriden lähttes, pölvast levitadas heinädme seikhid turptmaha kastkespäi. kaste heraštoitab olijoid bakterijoiden aktivižut pölvhan seikhiš. nene pened organizmad muretas klejindsubstancijoid kazmusen südäimes, a se azj abutab erigoitta kuidud seikhan pukasižes palaspäi. [num]ugoine process, pölvhan ligotamine kastkel, voib jätkatas severz' nedalid, sähä kacten. aigoitel'di pölvhan seikhid pidab käta tarkašti, miše kuidun ehtmine oliži ühtejiččen. erasiš küliš ligotihe pölvast joges. sadud piikoikhad kuidud letas da kuidas, a sid' kelikoitas da vidodas pästrišpäi erigoitten. [num]idodud pölvast harjatas koume kerdad, ka muga vedadas sišpäi puhtast kuidud — kebnašti kerttud hoikad lentad. kuiduspäi voib jo kezerta, kertta nitid. nitišpäi kudodas kanghid da sidodas kružavad. seikhišpäi sadas pölvazkuidud. semnišpäi sadas pölvazvoid vilul pressuindal. sömhä kävutadas pölvazvoid. sauvomha kävutadas kuidud, karpked, void. tekstil'tegimištho ottas kuidud tehmaha nitid, pölvazkanghid da kastumatomid kanghid, a sid' sobid-ki, vahapühkimid da toižid tegesid. keskaigaižed evropižed pirdajad panihe void kuvile hoštamha. kosmetikas sötmižmaskad pölvhaspäi abutadas siledoitta nahkan. pidab otta varunmujandad, sikš miše pölvazvoin sur' lugumär toksine om. amuižgrekalaižed teziba pölvhan semniden spravitajid ičendoid. gippokrat rekomendui kävutada sidä nälömakahiden koriden palatusen aigan. polvhan semnid zelläks kävutamha keratas ehttüd täuzin[http:herba.msu.rushipunovschoolbooksbotaniko-farmakognost_slovar[num].djvu блинова к.ф. и др. ботанико-фармакогностический словарь: справ.пособие под ред. к.ф. блиновой, г.п. яковлева. — м.: высш. шк., [num]. — [num]p. [num]aterial sauvomha pidab olda kuivan, lahotoman, siledan, senüdeta da korensöjita. kabaitud puid valitas, čapeltas parzikš suruden mödhe. pakutadud ladvoid kävutadas aluižikš. sid' kordäs parzid, ezmäižen kerdan ei lophusai, miše kuivoiži tazomäran. strubas parded pandas päleti. struban üks' rivi nimitase vencaks. saumoiden ühtenzoitusen mahtused: staučha — parziden agjad iškese, vai zamkha — korvusita, oma toižed-ki. ezmäine venc pandas sanktembaižiš parzišpäi. [num]encad kingitadas kesknezoi pazha, kudambad tehtas kaikuččen parden alahaspäi. pazan leveduz om [num]...[num] sm, se rippub klimataspäi mugažo. pazan parahim form om pol'ümbruz, a kaikiš hondomb form om koumesaumnik. erazvuiččed lämudenpidajad materialad kävutase pazoiden täutamha: amussai — samal, pölvazkabe, hob; nügüd'aigaižed — lentad džutanke pohjaks. pertin saudes vencad varmitadas kesknezoi pandud pil [num]-[num] sm korktusel, muga seinäd seištas vahvembikš. seiniš pid tehtas kaikuččel [num],[num]-[num] metral pardedme da šahmatjärgendusen mödhe struban korktusedme. pihoiš pid pandas toine toižen al. pertin sauvomižen lopun jäl'ghe ezmäižil [num]-[num],[num] vozil saudud seinäd išttas ičeze [num]-[num] korktusel pun kuivomižen da lämuzizoläcijan kingitamižen tagut. ozutesikš, sikš ku honusen korktuz podab olda [num] m lopuks, ka sauvomižen aigan strubad tehtas ülemb sidä [num]-[num] sm. sen ližaks, süvendust pin täht tehtas [num],[num]-[num] sm pit'kemb pid. puižen sauvusen iknan da uksen reiguiden al jättas erilišt keskustad ištumha [num] reigun korktusel. necidä keskustad täuttas lämudenpidajal materialal, a ištusen jäl'ghe sihe pandas brusuden da samaltas. saudas südäiseinid irdseinidenke sidoiš sadamha pit'kid saudud seinid seižujas olendas. nenid seinid sijatas, ozutesikš, kaikuttušt [num],[num] m irdaližen parden [num] sm sanktusenke da [num],[num] m — [num] sm sanktusenke. ku südäiseinita, a irdsein om pit'k, ka irdseinid vahvištadas ahtištandladlusil. [num]ilindruidud parz' — se om frezeruidud, kehker brus pazanke alahanpäi panemha edeližen vencan päle. nenid parzid ühtejiččen diametranke pil'däs erazvuiččen pidusen mödhe i eriližel ladlusel tehtas staučoid läz agjoid, a sid' tarkoiktašti čaptas pazad alahanpäi. tulese paloiden keraduz sauvomha, konstruktor ičesaz. se odvendab da kebnendab sauvomišt. kaikiš jügedambad operacijad mehaniziruidas, voib kirvezmehid sauvatoitta kacmata heiden mahtha. no om-ki todesižid vigoid: brusan kalibruindan aigan pun pindan pala heittas, se kucub lujetud haugelmasiden tegendad parziš da niiden kurčištundad, strub ištuse erazvuiččile süvüzile, jo eile voimust oigeta brusad seiniš pohjoižpolel irdale. nügüd'aigan üks' norvegižen sauvomižen tipišpäi otab populärižut [num]enämas. seinid panemha kävutadas pil'düd kaksiš polišpäi parzid, ei kehkrid parzid. pagištes norvegižes sauvomižes, [num]enäman sauvondkompanijad nimitadas pol'brusad paksus värin lafet:aks. saumad ühtenzoitmaha kehkran staučan sijas tehtas norvegišt zamkad[http:www.webcitation.org[num]a[num]oc тайна норвежского замка. — rus-plotnik.ru.] — nece om tilgunvuitte heitand peittud čokkoiduzpiden da pazanke. pol'brusad napridas tehta parzišpäi [num]-[num] sm poikheze da sen enamba, miše lujeta effektad. pol'brus tegese pardespäi kaksiden sel'gmaiden vastal'žel pilindal piloramas. [num]ai vesttas vai haugaidas čurid kirvhel, no nece azj om jügedamb. sadud sel'gmal ottas seinid, aidoid. pol'brusan pol'kehkrid pindoid kordäs, a lapakoid pindoid vol'däs elektrovolimel siledaks-vauktaks. jäl'ghine pord om pol'brusoiden panend strubaks. ümbriratud parz' pandas alahaižel pardel, azotadas molembid parzid lapakoil čuril. sid' pirtas pirdjäižel parden paza, pazad tehtas kädel eriližel kirvhel — vestimel. [num]uga pol'brusad išttas toine toižel kinktas, paza om levedambaine i voib panda äi lämudenpidajad materialad. sauvomha saumad zamkha, sauman ühtenzoitusen sijad märitas da pirtas äi kerdoid, ottas pumaterialad tautal läz staučan nägud, a sid' märitas da pirtas möst trapecijanvuiččid pirdoid, muga zamkan kontur tuleb-ki. kirvhel ottas tilgunvuittušt zamkad, sen pindoid siledoittas. ku zamk om vaumiž, ka tehtas üks' da enamba peittud pid ühtenzoitmaha ližaks alembaižen pardenke. pid tehtas kovas puspäi, ottas tautal kaks' süvendust vastaiti, sid' čokkoidas pid miččehe taht pardhe. südäiseiniš panda pid eile tarbhaižust. [num]ugoine piden panend ližadab pertile kovut da lämuzizoläcijad. [num]ugetas, miše norvegine zamk om paremb kehkert staučad. struban kuivamižen da ištmižen aigan se om kuti tilguiš, ned ei antkoi parzile käroutas ičeze südäikingitesišpäi. aigan mändes zamk vaiše vahveneb. kanadižen sauvomižen aigan parzid ühtenzoittas korktan tarkoiktusenke, piluid parziden keskes eile, stauč om trapecijanvuitte, seinäd nägudas järghižeks massivaks, lämudenpidajad materialad irdalpäi nägu ei. parzid kingitamha kävutadas erilišt znamastuzladlust. [num]ämudenpidai material sijadase pidust' part izoliruindkanalas. kaik londuseližed parden kandelmused jättas, se andab kaikuččele pertile, kaikuččele seinäle toštmatomut da individualižid pirdoid. parziden saumoiden ühtištoitused venudas kinktašti, eile millimetrad-ki piluid, se om punsauvojan parahim maht. parziden ičeze jüguz kinktoiden ühtištoitusidenke anttas pertile vahvut da varmdust. pun kova irdkaičendšoid om necen tehnologijan eriližuz, sen tagut seinäd ei kül'menzoikoiš läbi pakaižen aigan da seištas pit'kembaks strokuks. kaitud pun pind fil'truib il'mad oikti, sädab hüväd mikroklimatad sauvusen südäimes, andab kezal — vilud, tal'vel — lämäd. sen ližaks mugoine pumaterial seižub paremba ümbrišton painut vaste, vilik da senüt ei tulgoi, pu ei siništu, sen struktur vajehtase vähän päiväižen ul'traruskedsinižiden sädegiden painmižen al. tarbhaižed päinstrumentad strubad sauvomha: fail:oblo-angle.jpgsaudud staučha struban saum. fail:thist angle.jpgratud zamkha struban saum. fail:ood-srub-ship.jpgstruban parziden ühtištoituzelementad. fail:[num]arcass rounded timber alyans.jpgstrub cilindruidud parzišpäi. [num]l'mmassoiden sirdand om aperiodižiden vajehtusiden sü. ku tulijan il'mmassan parametrad ei kožugoi periodižiden vajehtusiden fazanke, ka sän kaikiš lujembad vajehtused tegese. aperiodižiden vajehtusiden intensivižuz poleneb korktushe mapindalpäi kactes. sänendustuz — se om vahvištoittud tedoližikš da tehnižikš ezimeletuz atmosferan tulijas olendas märitud tahol. järedoiden atmosferižprocessiden šingotesen analizan mödhe sätas endustust. [num]oz'tuhiden aigan ristitud naprihe sän endustada, no vaiše [num]. voz'sadal oficialižed sänendustused sünduiba. sädamha sänendustust — keratas verdandmusid meteostancijoil da kaimdajil atmosferan joksijas olendas. sid' projektiruidas atmosferan olendan vajehtusid endustuzmodeliden abul. kompjuterprogramad tehtas äjan, no ristitun ühtnemine om tarbhaine. ristit valičeb modelin šablon, hän keradab ühtheze edahaižid aigtegoid; mugažo modelin eriližused da jüvä oma tarbhaižed, pidab teta niid süväs. kävutadas severz' modelid kerdalaz, niiden andmusid ühtetas ližadamha endustusen tarkoiktust. äjad ristitud kävutadas sänendustusid ičeze eloho. torokan endustused oma tarbhaižed, sikš miše kaitas elod da varandad niiden abul. [num]ämuden da sadegiden endustused oma tarbhaižed maižandusen da sauvondsarakon radnikoile. [num]ämbituzverkoile pidab lämuden da tullein vägen endustust andmaha lämuzenergijan pästusen arvod tulijoile päivile. täuz' endustuz tariž sättutamha irdaližen voibištelendan da lebun planoid. kaik ristitud kävutadas sänendustust kaikuččen päivän sobmähäs oikti. [num]eteorologii tedoidab sän — nece om tedo atmosferan da sen olijoiden processiden polhe. [num]eteorologijan jagused: [num]ail'man meteorologine organizacii sättutab erazvuiččiden maiden meteokeskusiden radmižen. [num]eteoinformacijal om kaks' tipad: endustusiden ozaiduz rippub eziauguižes informacijaspäi päazjas. [num]enäman meteostancijoiden, meteo- da gidrologižiden postoiden avar verk om olmas. [num]eril da valdmeril tehtas kaclemižid eriližkalutadud laivoil. [num]l [num] kezakun [num]. päivän [num] valdkundoiden ezitajad allekirjutihe sidä, sen ližaks pol'šanma-ki sil-žo vodel redukun [num]. päivän. üro:n käskuzkirj tuli väghe vl [num] redukun [num]. päiväl, sidä oigetas üro:n päiväks. nece om nevondkundaline, direktividenandai da radonoigendai päorgan. se paneb üro:n päsekretarid radsijha [num]aruitomuden nevondkundan rekomendacijan mödhe. päsuiman ühtnijad keratas sessijoil, miččed oleldas regulärižed, eriližed da ekstraordinarižed eriližed. sügüz'kul koumandel tožnargel suiman jogavozne järgsessii avaidase. se radab ičeze ezimehen vai hänen ühten [num] varamehišpäi ohjandusen al päivjäl'gehen täudhe amundamižhe pohjhasai plenarižil ištundoil da päkomitetoil. [num]aruitomuden nevondkund om rahvahidenkeskeižen kožundan da varuitomuden kaičendan päorgan. kaikil üro:n ühtnijoil om velgusiš panda eloho sen pätandoid. kogoneb [num] valdkundad-ühtnijad: [num] — kaikenaigaižed, niil om kel'don oiktuz; [num] — pordaigaižed, niid valitas nevondkundha edelkirjutadud üro:n käskuzkirjas proceduran mödhe. necil organal toižed üro:n päorganad oma holiš. sekretariat paneb eloho niiden programid da politižid ohjandimid. täs [num] tuhad ristitud radab — hö oma rahvahidenkeskeižen personalan, ratas aluskundoiš kaiked mail'madme, vaumitas erazvuiččid jogapäiväližid üro:n azjoid. üro:n sekretariat abutab rados toižile üro:n organoile, tedištoitab da levitab üro:n dokumentoid, kaičeb arhivid, registriruib da pästab üro:n valdkundoiden-ühtnijoiden rahvahidenkeskeižid kožundkirjutesid. sekretariatan pämez' om üro:n päsekretar'. päsuim paneb händast radsijha [num]aruitomuden nevondkundan taričendan mödhe videks vodeks, kahtenden strokun om voimuz. nügüd'aigan jättud kirjutamata kožund om väges. sen mödhe üro:n [num]aruitomuden nevondkundan kaikenaigaižen valdkundan-ühtnijan rahvahanikale ei sa olda päsekretarin. nece om üro:n käskuzkundaline päorgan. sil om käskuzkundaližid da konsul'tirujid funkcijoid. [num]aiše valdkundoile sab olda azjoiden polikš käskuzkundaližen sel'gitamižen aigan. ku organizacijan ühtnii oli azjan poleks, ka kaikuččel mugoižel valdkundal om velgusiš panda eloho käskuzkundan pätandoid. käskuzkund kogoneb [num] ripmatont sudijad. nened sudijad tehtas ičeksaz, personaližikš, hö eile valdkundoiden ezitajad. sudijoile ei sa rata miččen taht toižen professijan mödhe. [num]čeze radon aigan käskuzkundan ühtnijad kävutadas diplomatižid privilegijoid da immunitetad. päsuiman, [num]aruitomuden nevondkundan da toižiden üro:n organoiden küzundan andmižen mödhe käskuzkund andab konsul'tativižid loppätandoid. nene loppätandad vaiše rekomenduidas, tetpašt väged eile. se paneb eloho üro:n funkcijoid ekonomižiš da socialižiš rahvahidenkeskeižiš ühthižtöiš. kogoneb [num] regionališt laudkundad: [num]l [num] kül'mkun [num]. päivän holenandai nevondkund jäti kesken ičeze radod, sikš miše üro:n jäl'gmäine olnu holenandmižes territorii, palau, vl [num] redukun [num]. päivän sai ičeze ripmatomut. nevondkund keradaškandese möst tarbhaižusen mödhe ičeze vai ičeze ezimehen pätandan jäl'ghe vai ičeze ühtnijoiden enambusen, päsuiman, [num]aruitomuden nevondkundan pakičendan mödhe. se pästab počtmarkoid da ünäižid kaluid dollarnominalanke üro:n uden jorkan ofisan täht, šveicarijan franknominalanke üro:n ženevan ofisan täht, evronominalanke üro:n [num]enan ofisan täht. nominalan suruz sättub valdkundan tarifoile necen sijatud üro:n ofisanke. üro:n käskuzkirjan mödhe, sen miččele taht päorganale upravimha ičeze velgusid sab panda erazvuiččiden abuorganoiden aluz. kaikiš tetabad abuorganoišpäi: ezmässai [num] valdkundad mülüiba üro:ha, ned allekirjutiba üro:n käskuzkirjad. nene valdkundad kaikiden ičeze kolonijoidenke da rippujiden territorijoidenke ezitiba läz kaiked mail'mad. aigan mändes kolonijad saiba ripmatomut, erased valdkundad jagoihe, i üro:n ühtnijoiden lugu ližadui. [num]hesai [num] kül'mkun [num]. päivhäsai jangon oli valdkundan pälidnaks, sid' sidä sirdihe naip'jidoho. jangon jäi valdkundan ižandusen, kul'turan da opendusen znamasižembaks keskuseks tähäsai.   kanghan mödnitiden sistem nimitase loimeks, a poikpoline — kudegeks. sättujid nitid nimitadas loimnitikš da kudelangoikš. kanghan sauvusen päozutajad: nitiden pletindan keskneze järgenduz; nitiden tiheduz. kudomha kangast, loimennitid da kudelangoid plettäs toine tošt järgenduses. nece järgenduz rippub nitiden tarbhaižes minimaližes verdaspäi vaumičemha kanghan pletindan kuvad. pletindankuva da rapport anttas kanghale strukturad, irdnägud da ičendoid. kanghan koveritomad pletindan kuvad oleldas paltnasižed, šaržasižed, satinaižed da kombiniruidud. tariž erištada kanghid sidotud paltnäspäi da kudomatomiš materiališpäi. kanghan tehmine nimitase kudondaks. kudomine om tekstil'paltnoiden vaumištamine kahtiden vastaimiži püštoiktoiden nit'sistemiden kuvadišel. kudomine om äipäličmänii process tobjimalaz. se mülütab nenid azjoid: vaumištamine kudomha, birbitand loimhe vai loimen sidond stavihe, kudomine ičesaz da gagurdusiden porotand kanghišpäi. kanghiden lopümbriradmine nimitase krepindaks, se mülüb himijan tehnologijoihe. krepind voib mülütada nenid operacijoid: pezend, šlihtuind, bukičend, vaugištoitand vai päidumine, merserizacii, mujutamine, išketamine, keričend, karvustamine, reljefan sädand. kanghiden merserizacii om kanghan lühüdaigaižen ümbriradmižen process sapižhe muglha panendal. sen jäl'ghe pestas kanghad hulal da vilul vedel. [num]erserizacii heitab kanghiden mujun kadotust, kaičeb eziauguižid ližamujuid da gigroskopižust dai varmdust, andab materialale šuukun polhe loštad. kanghiden išketamine om kirjaviden maiden samine vauktal vai mujutadud kanghal. nene mad sättudas materialan kävutandale. [num]šketamižen toižendad: oiged — vaugištoittud vai vauvhaks mujutadud kanghan pindale; travitud — mujutadud kanghale; rezervine — jättud mujutamata kanghale. kaikuččel kanghal om märitud ičendoid: faktur voib sättuda märitud tarbhaičendoihe: kanghad varmdusenke, kanghad eriližeta holeta, äikerdaižen kävutandanke. kanghan fakturan märhapanendas tariž erištada oiktad pol't murgnipolespäi. oiktan polen nägu om čomemb lujas, paremb mujegele; mugažo oiktan polen mujud oma eläbad vai loštakahamb, kuva om sel'ged. kaks'pol'žed kanghad oma olmas, niiden poled oma ühtejiččed, nitiden pletind om kaks'oiktaine — ozutesikš paltin, panam, kebnetud drapad. kaks'pol'žil villkanghil oiktan polen karvuz om lühüdamb. kävutadas erazvuiččid lühendusid znamoičemha sintetižid kanghid tegimištos da torguindas. ozutesikš, peps — poliesterkarvusenke, paoh — poliamidkangaz, popc — kabel' polipropilenaspäi. fail:stoffballen[num] fcm.jpgsanktoiden kanghiden palad. fail:stoffballen[num] fcm.jpghoikiden kanghiden palad.;[num]epsän kelen korpus;gost:ad  suviamerikan pälidnad - [num]ugažo erigoittas londuseline gaz sadud kivivoin ezmäižen fil'truindan aigan. [num]etan om londuseližen gazan päine da tarbhaine pala [num]-[num]% mülündanmäranke. sen ühtes metanan gomologad voidas olda mülündan paloikš: etan, propan da butan. jäl'gmäižiden kahtiden, a mugažo edembaižiden jügedambižiden gomologoiden olend om tahtota gazanveimes, sikš miše nened substancijad voidas tehtas nozoluzikš ümbrišton il'man lämudel. nozoluded sündudas vedenke gazgidratižid tüpid da umbištadas henoiden veimiden diametrad. [num]eden da ammiakveden olend om laskmatoi gazan mülündas. propan, metanan da acetilenan ülembad gomologad erigoittas gazanveimiden gazaspäi da kävutadas nozoltadud gazaks, kudambad voib pakuida da vedada miččel taht transportal. [num]uga voib kävutada metan-ki, vaiše painuz erineb: ahtištadud gaz om [num] atmosferan painudes, nozoltadud gaz — [num] atm. sättujad varuitomuden märad erinedas mugažo. tarbhaižed erazvuiččile kulutajile toižed substancijad oma londuseližen gazan paloikš; täuz' puhtastand polendab kommertišt ližad, i tarbiž vaiše käta kulutamižen varuitomaks: [num]onduseline gaz kändase kovaks olendaks makores. gaz ühtenzoitab mašoidun vedenke süvüdel, kus sur' gidrostatine painuz da järgeline lämuz oma olmas. [num]eden üks' mülünmär voib sidoda [num] gazanmülünmärad gidratan sündundan aigan. päazjas gazgidratoiden löudmižsijiden zonad levitadas igähižen rougun al da [num]an valdmeren pohjan al penil süvüzil. [num]onduseline gaz kävutase: [num]onduseline gaz om organižen poltusen kaikiš sel'ktemb toižend da elektrusen sandan üks' kaikiš puhthembiš mahtusišpäi. täuden palandan jäl'ghe vaiše vezipuru da hil'muiktuzgaz sündudas. hil'muiktuzgaz om toižen tipan redustandsubstancii — mugoine substancii om levitadud avaras londuses, no sen olemižen pala vajehtase ristitun radmižen tagut da vedase ekosisteman balansan hajendha. [num]etan da hil'muiktuzgaz kuctas kazmuzhonuzeffektad, sen taguiči pidab reguliruida niiden čudegiden mär. necen täht vl [num] kioton protokol om allekirjutadud. [num]odele [num] [num] valdkundad ratificirui sidä. nened valdkundad heittas [num]% kazmuzhonuzgazoid [num]as. [num]ugetas, miše londuseline gaz sündub [num]an koren sagedmaihe korktembil lämuzil da painuzil mi kivivoi. [num]ugoine azj todestab necidä: paksus gazan löudmižsijad venudas süvemb kivivoid. [num]onduseline gaz löudase ühtespäi severzihesai kilometrad süvüzil. hil'vezinikoiden znamasine mär om [num]an mantijas, no niiden samine om kal'hed lujas, sal'hetoi, sen tagut ei ole kommertišt mel'hetartust. [num]etan da erased toižed hil'vezinikad oma levitadud avaras kosmosas. [num]etan om koumanz' gaz ičeze levigandmižavaruden mödhe kaikes mail'mas vezinikan da gelijan jäl'ghe. äjad edembaižed päiväižespäi planetad da asteroidad mülütadas metanad jän, gazan da nozoluden olendoiš. [num]ugoižed kogod ei mülügoi londuseližen gazan löudmižsijihe. thumbright[num]pxburaudamižčuhunduz tehas-štatas, aü[num]. gaz sadas mansüvüzišpäi mareiguiden kal't. napridas sijata mareiguid tazomäras löudmižsijan kaiked territorijadme, miše mašoidun gazan painuz aleniži ühtejiččikš, toižin vezi voib putta mašoidhu. gaz om painudes mansüvüzil, se painuz ületab atmosferižen äjihe kerdoihe. pidab vaumitada mareiguišpäi tulijan gazan transportiruimha. [num]etkomponentad da segasubstancijad oma gazas. kaikutte metkomponent om ičeze kulutajan täht. segasubstancijad jügedas transportiruindad da kulutamišt. edel gazan andmišt vaumištadas veim: azotmašinoid kävutadas sädamha inertišt ümbrištod veimes. puhtastadas gazad da kuivatas sidä. päazjas gaz ajase veimiden kal't. gazanveim om optimaline transportiruimha londuselišt gazad peniš da keskmäižiš matkoiš. gaz pompase torviden kal't [num],[num] m da sen penemb diametral, [num] atm keskpainudes. [num]ikkudes veimen kal't gaz kadotab ičeze potenciališt energijad. nece energii kändase lämäks, konz gaz vägestab kidegen vägid torven seinän da ičeze šoiduiden keskes. sidä vizid, miše pidab sauda kompressorstancijoid gazanveimen märitud keskustoil. nenil stancijoil gaz ahtištase, sen painuz lujeneb [num] atmosferaspäi [num] atmosferhasai tobjimalaz, sid' gaz vilugoitase painuden alendusel. eriližed laivad-tankerad — gazanvedimed — kävutadas vemha edahaižiš matkoiš. [num]ugoižil laivoil gaz om nozoltadud olendas, izotermižiš bučiš -[num]...-[num]°[num] lämudenke. nozoltamha gaz vilugoitase korktas painudes. painuz oleleb [num] atm:hasai tarbhaižusiden mödhe. järgeline gazanvedim mülüb [num]-[num] tuh. m³. [num]äz allahabadad gang otab kaikiš znamasišt džamn-ližajoged oiktaspäi. päiči vähembusiš, rahvahanlugemižen aigan erištadas gruppid kelen i uskon mödhe, ei rahvahid. gangan basseinan ristitišt om segoitadud rodul, pagižeb erazvuiččil kelil, niid kaik om severz' kümnikad. kaikiš levitadud keled oma hindi, bengalan da anglijan keled. religijan mödhe regionan eläjad oma tobman palan induizman uskojad da islaman uskojad. [num]nduizman mifologijan mödhe, ganga om taivhaline jogi. se laskihe maha da kändihe gang-jogeks[http:www.rodon.orgotherr.htm#a[num] легенда о священной реке ганге рамаяна. — rodon.org.]. sil aigalpäi jogi jokseb koumes mirus läbi: taivaz, ma da ad. jogirandoil tehtas kremacijad, kolnuziden induizman uskojiden tuhk häiktudas veden päle, ristitud pestas dai čukloiteldas veron mödhe. joginiškoiden kos'ked oma raftingan populärižed da kaglanmurdajad sijad. päportad sijadase gangan suhišton randoil: kolkat [num]ndijas i [num]ongl, barisal, čandpur bangladešas.
